If he stays in Kuwait, in a country which essentially at the moment is rather like a prison camp, a country that he's dismantling day after day, then he will have to be forcibly removed, Major said. Major, just as unyielding in talking about Hussein as was his predecessor, Margaret Thatcher, rejected the notion that a partial Iraqi pullback from Kuwait would help bring about a solution to the crisis. British Prime Minister John Major said today that Iraqi troops will have to be forcibly removed from Kuwait if President Saddam Hussein does not agree to withdraw them peacefully. 